<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="941" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d941">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">New London,
                                    Conn.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July 27,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your telegram of the 22d
                            instant sanctioning the expenditure of money for the relief of United
                            States citizens at Habana, I have the honor to inform you that Her
                            Majesty’s acting consul-general at Habana has drawn upon you for the sum
                            of $500.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Jerome adds that the $2,000 which he is authorized to draw will be
                            sufficient for some time to come.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>